-- Canada’s Poloz to Address Lawmakers in Testimony June 6
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2013-06-03T16:57:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-03/canada-s-poloz-to-address-lawmakers-in-testimony-june-6.html
Bank of Canada Governor Stephen Poloz, who started on the job today, will testify at a
parliamentary committee on June 6.  Poloz will appear at the House of Commons Finance Committee
at 8:45 a.m. in Ottawa and testify for about two hours,
according to a notice on the central bank’s website.  Poloz was named the new governor on May 2 to replace  Mark
Carney , who left to take over the  Bank of England . Poloz,
57, was chief executive officer of Export Development Canada, a
government trade financing agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
 gquinn1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Fournier at 
 cfournier3@bloomberg.net  